Alfred WHITTELL v. George WHITTELL, Jr., et al. No. 8738. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Jan. 7, 1937. Vincent W. Hallinan and Carey Van Fleet, both of San Francisco, Cal., for appellant. George J. Hatfield, Harold C. Faulkner, Fred B. Wood, William B. Mead, and Jerome P. Herst, all of San Francisco, Cal., for appellees.

Before GARRECHT, MATHEWS, and HANEY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, and good cause-therefor appearing, ordered appeal herein dismissed, that a judgment of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and the mandate of this court issued forthwith.
